Maintainer: Jeanne Clément <jeanne.clement16@laposte.net>
Description: MadaClim provides a set of climatic and environmental rasters
    for French Guiana that can be used for ecological analyses. Data comes
    from a variety of sources (WorldClim, Chelsa, Metéo France for the climate,
    and SRTM, BRGM, various research projects for the envronment). Rasters are
    available at 1km resolution in UTM 22N (epsg: 32622) and cover all the
    territory of French Guiana (extent is xmin=100000, ymin=230000,
    xmax=435000, ymax=642000).
URL: https://ecology.ghislainv.fr/guyaclim
